Starting with the bam file containing all reads mapped against the chr 1 reference:

Extract only reads where both the read and it's mate are aligned:
samtools collate -u -O Seidman751_chr36.bam | samtools fastq -F 12 -1 Seidman751_chr36_1.fq -2 Seidman751_chr36_2.fq -0 /dev/null -s /dev/null -n

New fastq files contain 420214 reads.

Map these back to the chr 1 reference to check that these are what we want:
hisat2 -p 6 -k 1 --no-spliced-alignment -x ../../../genome_diploid_index/genome_diploid_chr36 -1 Seidman751_chr36_1.fq -2 Seidman751_chr36_2.fq 2> Seidman751_chr36.log | samtools view -bS | samtools sort -T Seidman751_chr36 > Seidman751_chr36.bam
samtools index Seidman751_chr36.bam

Log shows 100% of reads mapped.
